fferent weather conditions ({{weather|rain}}, {{weather|sandstorm}}, and {{weather|harsh sunlight}}, respectively).\n** They are also the only Pokémon with Solar Power that cannot learn {{m|Solar Beam}} or {{m|Sunny Day}}.\n\n===Origin===\nHelioptile is probably based on {{wp|Chlamydosaurus|frilled-neck lizard}}s, though its frills also resemble those found on \'\'{{wp|Phrynocephalus mystaceus|secret toad-headed agama}}\'\'. It may also be based on the {{wp|spotted salamander}}, a salamander that can {{wp|photosynthesize}}. Its ability to learn {{m|Surf}} may be a reference to the {{wp|common basilisk}}, a reptile capable of running on water for short distances. Like what its German name suggests, Helioptile may be based on the {{wp|iguana}} too. Additionally, it shares few resemblances to the {{wp|leopard gecko}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nHelioptile is a combination of ἥλιος \'\'{{wp|helios}}\'\' (Ancient Greek for sun), \'\'heliophile\'\' (organism attracted to large amounts of sunlight), and \'\'reptile\'\'.\n\nErikiteru may be a combination of \'\'{{wp|elekiter}}\'\', エリマキトカゲ \'\'erimaki tokage\'\' (frill-necked lizard), and 照る \'\'teru\'\' (to shine).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=electric|type2=normal\n|ja=エリキテル \'\'Erikiteru\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'{{wp|elekiter}}\'\', {{tt|エリマキトカゲ \'\'erimaki tokage\'\'|frill-necked lizard}}, and {{tt|照る \'\'teru\'\'|to shine}}\n|fr=Galvaran|frmeaning=From \'\'{{wp|galvanism|galvanisme}}\'\' and the genus \'\'{{tt|Varanus|Monitor lizard}}\'\'\n|es=Helioptile|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Eguana|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|elektrisch|electric}}\'\' and \'\'iguana\'\'\n|it=Helioptile|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=목도리키텔 \'\'Mokdorikitel\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|목도리도마뱀 \'\'mokdori\'domabaem\'\'|frilled-neck lizard}} and \'\'elekiter\'\'\n|zh_yue=發電蜥 \'\'Faatdihnsīk\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|發電 \'\'faatdihn\'\'|to generate electricity}} and {{tt|蜥 \'\'sīk\'\'|lizard}}\n|zh_cmn=傘電蜥 \'\'Sǎndiànxī\'\'|zh_c